  "text": "The linear result (34b) holds only for C 1 = C L , which is (unsurprisingly) the same condition that we obtained from requiring (34a). Now, using equation (40), we can compare equations (35) and (29). We see that the bcc operator must have conformal weight 1 2 λ 2 (this was already discussed in [CITATION_1] ) and that C 1 must be zero. Thus, interestingly, while we can assume any C 1 to construct a SFT, only for C 1 = 0 will this solution have a primary bcc operator.",
